dcterms:description: The occupancy grid map is widely adopted for probabilistic localization and mapping in robotics. It is constructed by partitioning the range under consideration into grid elements, allowing for the representation of the uncertainty of the predicted trajectory with probability.
dcterms:title: Occupancy Grid Map

dcterms:description: Trajectory data collected from highway driving, used to train the LSTM model for predicting vehicle trajectories based on sensor measurements.
dcterms:title: Trajectory Data from Highway Driving

dcterms:description: Vehicle trajectory data used for training the LSTM model, focusing on the motion of surrounding vehicles based on sensor measurements.
dcterms:title: Vehicle Trajectory Data
